## Confirmation Modals (ConfirmModal)

Use **ConfirmModal** (`@/components/Feedback/ConfirmModal`) only for destructive, irreversible, or consequential actions.

- **Use for:** Delete (category, product, coupon, user deactivation, etc.), cancel order, reject payment; status changes that end a flow (e.g. mark order cancelled/returned); bulk/admin actions (approve/reject shop, moderate review).
- **Do not use for:** Normal create/edit (use toasts); navigation/filters; reversible actions with undo.

**Pattern:** Local state for visibility (e.g. `confirmAction: null | "cancelled"`). Pass `title`, `message`, `confirmLabel`, `cancelLabel`, `onConfirm`, `onCancel`, `variant="destructive"` for destructive. In `onConfirm`: run mutation, toast, then clear state to close.

---

## Tooltips

Use **Tooltip** (`@/components/Feedback/Tooltip`) to clarify without cluttering. Radix-based; Geist-style placement/delay.

- **Use for:** Icon-only buttons (pair with `aria-label` and same text in tooltip); truncated text or abbreviations (full text in tooltip); secondary controls (e.g. "Copy ID").
- **Do not use for:** Buttons/links with visible text; critical info that must always be visible.

**Pattern:** `<Tooltip content="Label text">` wrapping trigger; default `side="top"`, `sideOffset={6}`, `delayDuration={300}`. Keep `aria-label` and tooltip `content` in sync for icon buttons.

---

## Industrial Best Practices

- **Design system:** One typography scale, one color token set, one spacing/radius/shadow system. Avoid one-off values so the UI stays consistent and theming stays maintainable.
- **Accessibility:** Semantic HTML first; sufficient contrast; focus states and keyboard flow; icon-only controls get visible labels (tooltip + aria-label). Test with keyboard and screen reader when adding new patterns.
- **Tables:** Same structure and filter row order on every list page so behavior is predictable and components can be reused. Server-side filtering and pagination only; no frontend-only filtering of large datasets.
- **Feedback:** Clear rule: modals for high-stakes confirmations, toasts for result feedback. Use ListLoading/DetailsLoading instead of ad-hoc spinners so loading UX is consistent.
